						<div class="title">
							<h1>Krebs on his cycle</h1>						
						</div>
                        
						
						<div class="caption">
						
						<p><img alt="image" src="http://media.tumblr.com/2875d86865560aeabcbe1c92984f6f4b/tumblr_inline_mtzw3mVwU71snsdec.jpg"/></p>
<p>A groaner for sure, but I had to do it.  Picture of Hans Krebs, Nobel laureate and discoverer of metabolic processes such as the urea cycle and the citric acid cycle (also known as the Krebs cycle).  Responsible for making me think biochemical reactions literally occurred as a series of rotating circles in cells until I was a 21-year old college student.     </p>
						
